    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "Carved with stylized images of water or aquatic life, *depth charges* that are fired underwater or at a submerged target function with their normal range increments and can hit no matter their normal damage type. This ammunition explodes if it hits a target underwater, dealing bludgeoning damage in a 20-foot burst (basic Fortitude save) according to its type. This burst doesn't extend out of the water.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 36,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "07336d377bbfcf8d760f34f32f513526",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Consumable",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 454,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "An item with this trait can be used only once. Unless stated otherwise, it\u2019s destroyed after activation. Consumable items include alchemical items and magical consumables such as scrolls and talismans. A character can Craft consumable items in batches of four.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
